{
  "_comment": "Levels 1-5, authored by hand rather than generated, so the first five boards teach the rule on purpose instead of leaving a player's first impression to chance. Each one adds exactly one idea. They sit on the same 11x11 board the easy tier uses, so the campaign opens at the size it goes on with — the teaching comes from how few arrows there are and how they are placed, not from a smaller grid. Verified by levels.test.ts like every other level.",
