    {
      "_teaches": "ONLY THE HEAD'S LANE COUNTS. a1 bends: its tail runs right along row 3, and a2 sits squarely in front of that tail. a1 is still free, because its HEAD is in row 4 and row 4 is clear ahead of it. The tail leaves by retracing the head's route. Meanwhile a3 really is blocked — by a1's body. This is the rule people get wrong.",
